"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-02-Watching-Olympic-Games-at-cinemas-becomes-new-China-trend-1vJwhntCgnK-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  The 2024 Paris Olympics are in full swing. For Chinese audiences, watching the competition live at the cinema is an increasingly popular option.  Starting with the opening ceremony last week, cinemas across the country are rolling out the service, allowing sports fans to cheer for Team China together in a public space, just as if they were in Paris.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"